  "prompt": "How is parfum/perfume made?",
  "response": "Perfume is made through a complex process involving several key steps:\n\n1. Ingredient Sourcing\n- Natural ingredients: Essential oils from flowers, fruits, herbs, woods, and resins\n- Synthetic ingredients: Artificially created aromatic compounds\n\n2. Extraction Methods\n- Steam distillation: Heating plant materials to extract essential oils\n- Cold pressing: Mechanical extraction, often used for citrus peels\n- Solvent extraction: Using chemical solvents to extract delicate fragrances\n- Enfleurage: Traditional method using fats to capture flower scents\n\n3. Fragrance Composition\n- Perfumers (called \"noses\") blend ingredients into three layers:\n- Top notes: First scents detected, light and volatile\n- Middle notes: Emerges after top notes dissipate\n- Base notes: Longest-lasting, foundation of fragrance\n\n4. Mixing\n- Combining extracted oils with alcohol (usually 70-95%)\n- Precise measurements and proportions\n- Filtering to ensure clarity\n\n5. Aging\n- Allowing fragrance to mature and blend\n- Can take weeks to months\n- Helps develop complex, harmonious scent\n\n6. Bottling\n- Packaging in decorative bottles\n- Quality control and final testing\n\nEach perfume is a unique artistic creation involving scientific precision and creative skill.",
